ðŸ”¹ Intermediate Operations (returns a Stream)

Method	    Meaning / Usage
filter()	  Filters elements based on a condition
map()	      Transforms elements
flatMap()	  Flattens nested structures (like List of Lists)
distinct()	Removes duplicates
sorted()	  Sorts elements
peek()	    Performs action on each element (used for debugging)
limit()	    Limits number of elements
skip()	    Skips first n elements



ðŸ”¹ Terminal Operations (ends the stream pipeline)
Method	  Meaning / Usage
forEach()	    Performs action for each element
toArray()	    Converts stream to array
collect()	    Collects elements to List, Set, Map, etc.
reduce()	    Reduces stream to a single value
count()	      Counts elements
min() / max()	Gets min or max element (based on Comparator)
anyMatch()	  Checks if any element matches condition
allMatch()	  Checks if all elements match condition
noneMatch()	  Checks if no element matches condition
findFirst()	  Gets the first element (Optional)
findAny()	    Gets any element (Optional)
